error
If a reference does not point to any object, it holds null, and accessing members will cause a NullPointerException.

passing object refernce in argument
_____________________________________

class A
{
	int x,y;
	A(int p,int q)
	{
		x=p;
		y=q;
	}
	static void show(A obj)
	{
             System.out.println(obj.x+" "+obj.y);
	}
}

class Test
{
	
	public static void main(String arg[])
	{

	 
            A  ob=new A(10,20);
	     A.show(ob); //passing obect refernce in argument

	}
}


