what are in change normal variable not change in origanal value   (call by value)

This is a perfect demonstration of Call by Reference and Call by Value in Java



class A
{
	int x,y;
	A(int p,int q)
	{
		x=p;
		y=q;
	}
	static void show(A obj) //call by refernce
	{
             System.out.println(obj.x+" "+obj.y); //10 20
             obj.x=30;
             obj.y=40;
	}
	static void disp(int m)  //call by value
	{
		System.out.println(m); // 50
		m=60;
	}
}

class Test
{
	
	public static void main(String arg[])
	{

	     
            A  ob=new A(10,20);
	     A.show(ob); //passing obect refernce in argument
	     System.out.println(ob.x+" "+ob.y); // 30 40 
            int n=50;
            A.disp(n);
            System.out.println(n);

	}
}


10 20
30 40
50
50


Concept	         Object Reference (A ob)	Primitive (int n)
Passed by	    Value of reference (address)	Value (copy of data)
Can modify original?	✅ Yes	                    ❌ No
Affected after method?     	Yes	                      No





